TopicTitle: .9 Started crashing all of a sudden

Articles.Content:
We'll need some more information. If you have any mods from before you installed 0.90, you may want to check that they have indeed been removed. Once the issue is resolved, then you can find updated versions of the mods for 0.90.

We need an output_log.txt and DxDiag at mininum. If you're not sure where to find these files, please see the Stock Support sticky thread.

Same error output here! Thus I suspect it's the same problem? Correct me if I'm wrong.

Mine would crash while loading as long as there was an existing settings.cfg file, and would run fine while that file still existed AFTER it had loaded already. But then when it was closed and started up again with the file, it would crash. Delete the file, and it starts up fine. Odd problem, minor inconvenience . . .

- - - Updated - - -

I can get an output log and all the other error information tomorrow. Cheers!

Edited December 26, 2014 by vexx32
I even reinstalled .25 to see if it was just .9 that wasnt behaving. But it wont load all the way either.

You're running out of memory. Try setting the TEXTURE_QUALITY to half or less. This should be the default value now in v0.90, but perhaps there is something odd about the way it saves it when you exit the game, if you didn't set it yourself.

It sounds as though the both of you may have some permissions issues. It'd be a good idea to make sure that the KSP folder (and all files within it) allow read/write/modify permissions, at the least. It's also possible that an antivirus is denying KSP access to the settings file while it checks what KSP is doing. You can add KSP to your antivirus' exception list to test this.
